Looks like there is a discrepancy between *runtimeName* and *version* which studio fetches from the Appc Daemon iOS info.

As you can see in the below content, runtimeName shown as "iOS 11.4" and "version" shown as "11.3"

{code:java}
"11.3": [
{

"deviceDir": "/Users/kkolipaka/Library/Developer/CoreSimulator/Devices/BB9DFC87-10A6-466A-8D47-C854C872AAF8",

"deviceType": "com.apple.CoreSimulator.SimDeviceType.iPad-Air",

"name": "iPad Air",

"runtime": "com.apple.CoreSimulator.SimRuntime.iOS-11-4",

"udid": "BB9DFC87-10A6-466A-8D47-C854C872AAF8",

"type": "ios",

"deviceName": "iPad Air",

"family": "ipad",

"model": "iPad4,2",

"runtimeName": "iOS 11.4",

"version": "11.3",

"supportsWatch": {

"9.4:9F1027a": false

},

"supportsXcode": {

"9.4:9F1027a": true

},

"watchCompanion": {}

},
{code}

Please find the attached Appc Daemon output for {{appc appcd exec /ios/1.x/info}}
 [^gistfile1.txt] 

Which is having only 11.3 iOS simulators.

Please also find the output for ti info iOS command {{appc ti info -o json -t ios > tiinfo_ios.txt}}
 [^tiinfo_ios.txt] 

Interestingly, ti info is having both the 11.3 and 11.4 simulators
